From b1edf3daaf1994d63c30f788b8abe0d19caa8ec1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peter Hutterer <peter.hutterer@who-t.net>
Date: Fri, 19 Dec 2025 15:52:48 +1000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] gdk/wayland: process the data from the iterator, not the
 list head

Where more than one event was pending in the queue the second one never
got processed. This caused e.g. tablet proximity events on other
compositors to be broken - mutter sends the proximity in its own frame
(hence only one element in the list) but other compositors send it
together with motion/distance/pressure (hence two events). On those
compositors the proximity was passed to the application twice while the
motion event was ignored.

Fixes: 237738028639e0238ec2a30a34987d5ab7311a83
Closes #7793

Part-of: <https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gtk/-/merge_requests/9286>
(cherry picked from commit dc0c135f255ce0f6618e4cf8548819de0e439474)
---
 gdk/wayland/gdkseat-wayland.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/gdk/wayland/gdkseat-wayland.c b/gdk/wayland/gdkseat-wayland.c
index 19e0609771..dfb6ba1d59 100644
--- a/gdk/wayland/gdkseat-wayland.c
+++ b/gdk/wayland/gdkseat-wayland.c
@@ -2785,7 +2785,7 @@ gdk_wayland_tablet_flush_frame_events (GdkWaylandTabletData *tablet,
 
   for (l = events; l; l = l->next)
     {
-      TabletEvent *tablet_event = events->data;
+      TabletEvent *tablet_event = l->data;
       GdkEvent *event = NULL;
 
       if (!tablet->current_tool)
